    "body": "### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.7.0\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArchLinux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nAlacritty\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nalacritty\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo\n\n### How to reproduce the issue\n\n1. `nvim --clean -u crash.lua`\r\n\r\n\r\n`cat crash.lua`\r\n```lua\r\nlocal Error = {}\r\nError.__index = Error\r\n\r\nfunction Error.new(msg)\r\n    local o = setmetatable({}, Error)\r\n    o.msg = msg\r\n    return o\r\nend\r\n\r\nfunction Error:__tostring()\r\n    return tostring(self.msg)\r\nend\r\n\r\nlocal function setTimeout(ms)\r\n    local timer = vim.loop.new_timer()\r\n    timer:start(ms, 0, function()\r\n        timer:stop()\r\n        timer:close()\r\n        error(Error.new('timeout'))\r\n        -- error() also crash\r\n    end)\r\n    return timer\r\nend\r\n\r\nsetTimeout(1000)\r\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nprint `timeout`\n\n### Actual behavior\n\ncrash",
